hey all so ya... its kinda been awhile..maybe like a week...but still...i hope everyones Halloween was good!! mine was! On Friday i went to lazer quest w/ Katie, Katie's cousin, and Katie's frenchy!!! it was soooo much fun b/c we got to play a game with just us four. It was kinda scary b/c there was 4 of us in a huge, dark place with loud scary music playing...but it was still fun. On Saturday i went to Alicia's bday party at bjs. It was...interesting, but very fun! I had a really good time!!! HAPPY BIRTHDAY ALICIA!!! Then i came home and went to bed and Ben called me at like 11:30 b/c he had just gotten home from Big Toe. So i talked to him for awhile. Then on Saturday i got up and went to church and then after that Ben and I went to go see the Grudge. The movie itself was terrible, but it still kinda scared me! I was squeezing Ben's arm so hard i'm suprised i didn't break it off!!! Then after that i went to go work at the Fall Festival at church. It was fun! Ben and i worked the balloon pop thingy but the stupid plastic darts kept breaking so i had to go home and get real darts...ya that was interesting watching little 1st graders throwing these sharp things at balloons....sigh good times good times!!! lol!!
OOOH!!! and tomorrow is Ben and my 1yr and 4 mnth anniversary!!! yippee!! lol its crazy!!! 1 year and 4 months!! man thats a long time-especially for my 1st boyfriend!! Ya i'm sooooooooooo(times infinity) lucky to be with such an awesome guy! He's an AMAZING Christian guy who treats girls with respect, and can make me laugh even if i'm in the worst mood ever! He is just an EXTREMELY AWESOME guy!!i love him so much!!

k well i'm all typed out lol so.....see ya later!!

wow so ya its been awhile since i've written anything in my journal!!! not that anyone really reads it anyway....so lets see......whats been happening....October1 was Ben's birthday....and he enlisted into the army and he's leaving in June...even though its far away it seems so soon...i'm gonna miss him...but i'm not gonna get into that cuz i'll be writing forever...so ya Ben's birthday was a lot of fun we went to el palenque and about 30 people showed up...it was CRAZY!!! it was alot of fun... tee hee my cake was the best ever!! lol!!! hmm...lets see..October 7 i went to some PALs thing at church...that was interesting...thats all i can say about it...interesting. Then that weekend was BIG TOE!!!! woop!!! it was sooo amazing!!! HEY GUYS WHO DID THE ZIPLINE?? OH YA I DID THE ZIPLINE!!!!! sry i'm proud of myself lol...it was sooo cool i loved worshipping under the stars..its so cool how God cleared up the night sky so we could see all of the stars...I saw 2 shooting stars!!!! it was amazing!!! God really showed me a lot that weekend...very cool. Lets see.... OOOOOO Tomorrow i FINALLY get my license!!!! I am sooooo excited about that!!!! I finally get to drive to ABS by myself!!! woop!!!!! so excited!! i'm soo gonna go driving extremely fast w/ my music blaring and my windows rolled down...cuz i finally can!!!! woop!! sry just a little excited about it lol. Oh and i'm pretty excited about halloween!! i'm gonna be a tiger...lol i bought a really cool headband that has a tiger nose coming from it that covers my nose and it just looks awesome...ya just gotta see it... ummm...i don't really have much else to talk about sooooo i'm gonna go now...adios!!!

hey hey hey all!!! today was a nothing day...it wasn't terrible and it wasn't great...it was just a day... like i posted previously, tuesdays have no meaning!! they are just blah nothing important happening kind of days. OOOOh  but today i found out something that is incredibly awesome!!! Ok for PALs we have some like character...building.......thing...... anyway the important part is that it falls on Thursday October 7(my brothers bday by the way), so we get to miss the entire day of school for it. Well we get that Friday off as well as the following Monday...so i get a 5 day weekend!!!!! HAHA take that suckas!!! lol... Oh and the whole thing is going to be held at Houston Northwest Church!!! even better!!!! So while all you guys are at school, i'm gonna be having loads of fun at the best church ever!! lol. And that weekend is also Big Toe weekend!!! Man i just can't wait for October!!! here are my plans for Oct.:

  1. October 1st: Ben's 18th Birthday!! and its a friday
  2. October 5th: Our 1yr and 3 month anniversary (15 months)
  3. October 6th: My dog's birthday (yes i know when it is! lol)
  4. October 7th: My brother's birthday and the PALs thingy (No school for me!!)
  5. October 10th and 11th: Big Toe!!!!
  6. October 20th: I FINALLY get my license!!!!
  7. October 31st: Halloween!!!!

So ya October is gonna be a fun and eventful month!!! I CAN'T WAIT ANYMORE!!!

17 more days until the action filled month starts!!! yay!!!!

so today at like 1 i got my hair cut and rehighlighted!!!!! instead of getting my red highlights, i got auburn colored streaks in my hair. OMGosh it looks sooooo cool!!!! I love it!!!!!

Today is a day that will forever dwell in my heart and mind. My mom, brother and i went to taco bell for lunch. In the middle of us eating this homeless lady walked in, the ONLY thing she had with her was her Bible. She sat down at the table next to us and started reading it. A lady had been standing in line and just received her food and walked over to the homeless lady and gave her two tacos. The homeless lady immediately grabbed her chest and pulled her cross necklace from under her blouse. She turned to us and said, "God sure works in mysterious ways" Wow that seriously tugged at my heart. She told us that she was in there just trying to get out of the heat because she almost passed out b/c of how hot it was. My mom went up to the counter and asked for a complimentary cup so she could give the lady some water. The guy behind the counter, he looked about 17 or 18, asked if it was for the lady. My mom told him it was, thinking that he wasn't going to let her get the water for the lady, but instead he reached for the larger sized drink instead of the complimentary cup and told my mom to give her anything she wants. The lady was just so excited! She said how truly blessed she was. When she said that i couldn't help to cry. Here is this homeless lady who has probably not eaten in a few days sitting in a Taco Bell reading the Bible and praising the Lord!!! It just shows what Chris was talking about at Church, this homeless lady had planted a seed in all of us there at Taco Bell. She taught me a lesson. She has almost nothing worth money, but she has the most precious possession, a relationship with Christ. I don't think i could ever forget today...it really impacted my life.
GOD IS LIKE A GIANT STRESS BALL!!!!!

wow the physics test....not bad at all!!! i was so worried over nothing!!! wow i just feel so relaxed right now. yesterday i was flippin out and so worried about EVERYTHING but now i'm just cool and happy. God is soooo amazing!! i was so stressed but He just calmed me down. One because in Teen Leadership today we had a "campfire" which was really logs w/ christmas lights wrapped around them, and we just answered some questions. It was so relaxing and comforting to hear what other people value in their lives. It just relieved all of my stress!! It's so amazing b/c God knew that i had that physics test today and that i would be driving myself insane worrying about it so he allowed my mind to be taken off of physics and enjoy a day of relaxation in teen leadership.

GOD IS AMAZING!!!!!

michelle gave me this really cool quote thingy and i absolutely love it!!!!! 

this is how it goes:

  "girls are like apples on trees, the best ones are at the top. Most boys don't want to reach for the good ones b/c they are afraid of falling and getting hurt. Instead, they just get the rotten apples that are on the ground, that aren't as good, but easy. So the apples at the top think there is something wrong w/ them when in reality they are amazing. so ya its tuesday....terrific tuesday....right. ya know how everybody hates mondays? i think everyone should hate tuesdays. here is my reasoning....

monday is the beginning of the week which means that anything could happen. monday determines whether or not you'll have a good week...therefore mondays should be enjoyed.

wednesday is the day that churches usually have their youth groups which provide as a venting day where you can get support from others your own age. it is also the middle of the week so once you reach wednesday you know you made it half way.

thursday is a good day because after thursday is friday!!! so once you get past thursday everything is just peachy

friday...well everyone loves friday because after school is the weekend!!!!

but tuesday....tuesday is a nothing day... there is nothing exciting about tuesday....

so don't hate mondays!! hate tuesdays!!!!

ya after reading my subject i'm sure most of you are thinking i mean my boyfriend. Wrong!! I'm talking about a 100% Perfect guy to ever live! If i'm not talking about my boyfriend then who on earth could i be talking about?! Well that's the cool part because the guy i'm talking about isn't on earth; he is in heaven. The guy i'm talking about is named Jesus Christ. He is the ONLY perfect guy to ever walk on the face of the earth. He came to earth, lived a sinless(perfect) life, and died on the cross so that you and i might have a chance to go to heaven.

"Very rarely will anyone die for a righteous man, though for a good man someone might possibly dare to die. But God demonstrates his own love for us in this: While we were still sinners, Christ died for us." -Romans 5:7&8.

while there are those of you who think that your boyfriends are perfect guys, you are very very very wrong! ONLY Jesus Christ is the perfect man, which is why i am in absolute head over heels in love with Him!!! I'm absolutely CRAZY for Him!!! What can i say, I'm a Jesus Freak!!!

lol yup! yesterday i turned the big ONE-SEVEN!!! lol ya it was an AWESOME day!!!!! k so while all of you guys had to wake up early to do various things, i was sleeping soundly in my comfortable bed!!! tee hee!! So when i finally decided to get out of bed i took a long relaxing shower and then blow dried my hair and got dressed. Then my mommy took me to go and get my permit b/c i'm dumb and still don't have my license! but any way i got my permit (it took me 2 times to pass the test!! lol) So after that, my mom and i went to taco bell to celebrate, and for once i got to drive home from taco bell (legally(lol)) So we got home and i realized hey i wanna go driving again! so my mom and i went driving around "with no particular place to go" When we got home i watched my favorite show Yu-Gi-Oh w/ my twin(Football(Erin Irvin))and then at like 5:30 i followed her home in my beautiful baby(my mustang)and then drove back home.

After that, i came home and got dressed and then went to go pick up Ben to go out to eat with my family at El Palenque. We go there every year for my bday b/c they always put whipped cream in my face and sing me happy birthday in spanish! Ya its always a blast! But last night was just so much better b/c i was with my AMAZING boyfriend! After we ate at El Palenque, Ben came over and we watched the Princess Bride together. I absolutely love that movie lol. Ya it was just sooooooooooooooooo great b/c the MOST AWESOME guy EVER was holding me in his arms. (tee hee i'm feeling all girly inside!! lol!) I am just the luckiest girl ever!!!! My birthdays are usually good, but yesterday was by far the BEST birthday ever!!!!!!

Hmmm...how to begin a journal such as this... 

Yesterday at around 4:00 pm, I heard the terrifying news that Scott Larson had been killed in Iraq. I was stricken with disbelief. How could this happen?? My heart and prayers go out to the Larson family. I have no idea what they must be going through, I just pray that God comforts them throughout the whole thing. Scott Larson lost his life fighting to keep ours safe. He is a hero in my eyes. His death was a very noble death. Lets not be brought down by his death, let us rejoice! For now he is in the BEST place possible sitting next to our Creator. God had planned this way back in the past, before we even knew Scott or any of the Larson's. Thats got to be a comforting thing. 

Scott, I never officially met you, but you are my brother in Christ and I love you very much and want to thank you for everything you have unknowingly done for me. You are truly and inspiration!I can't wait to get to heaven so I can meet you.
